INSERT INTO `wp_em_events` VALUES (2,23627,'dragon-boat-festival',1887,1,'Dragon Boat Festival','00:00:00','00:00:00',1,'2017-05-30','2017-05-30','Dragon Boat Festival, also known as Duanwu Festival, is a traditional and important celebration in China. Dragon Boat Festival 2017 falls on May 30 (Tuesday). China will have 3 days of holiday from Sunday (May 28) to Tuesday (May 30), and we will be back at work on Wednesday, June 4.\r\n<h3>Dragon Boat Festival Facts.</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"drop1\">\r\n	<li><strong>Chinese:</strong> 端午节 Duānwǔ Jié /dwann-woo jyeah/ \'start [of the] fifth traditional solar month [June 6 to July 6] festival\'</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Date:</strong> month 5 day 5 of the Chinese lunar calendar</li>\r\n	<li><strong>History:</strong> over 2,000 years</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Celebrations:</strong> dragon boat racing, health-related customs, honoring Qu Yuan and others</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Popular festival food:</strong> sticky rice dumplings (<em>zongzi</em>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLearn more <a href=\"http://www.chinahighlights.com/festivals/dragon-boat-festival-fact.htm\" target=\"_blank\">facts about the Dragon Boat Festival</a>\r\n<h2>What Is China\'s Dragon Boat Festival?</h2>\r\nIt\'s a folk festival full of traditions and superstitions, maybe originating from dragon worship; an event on the sporting calendar; and a day of remembrance/worship for Qu Yuan, Wu Zixu, and Cao E.\r\n\r\nThe festival has long been a traditional holiday in China. On May 20th 2006 it was selected into the first batch of National Intangible Cultural Heritage items. In 2008 it was first celebrated as a public holiday in China. And on October 30th 2009 it was added to the UNESCO World Intangible Cultural Heritage List.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://uploads-demo.getpop.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/06/Dragon_boat_racing_in_Hong_Kong.jpg\" data-size=\"1296x968\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-23626\" src=\"https://uploads-demo.getpop.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/06/Dragon_boat_racing_in_Hong_Kong-640x478.jpg\" alt=\"Dragon_boat_racing_in_Hong_Kong\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Dragon Boat Racing — from legend to sporting event!</h2>\r\nDragon boat racing is said to originate from the legend of people paddling out on boats to seek the body of patriotic poet Qu Yuan (343–278 BC), who drowned himself in the Miluo River.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gxGXM7z_OBM\r\n\r\nDragon boat racing is <strong>the most important activity during the Dragon Boat Festival</strong>. The wooden boats are shaped and decorated in the form of a <a href=\"http://www.chinahighlights.com/travelguide/article-chinese-dragons.htm\">Chinese dragon</a>. The boat size varies by region. Generally it is about 20–35 meters in length and needs 30–60 people to paddle it.\r\n\r\n<strong>During the races</strong>, dragon boat teams paddle harmoniously and hurriedly, accompanied by the sound of beating drums. It is said that the winning team will have good luck and a happy life in the following year.\r\n\r\nDragon boat races are a major sporting event in many places, which competitors train hard for.',0,NULL,'00:00:00',0,0,4,NULL,NULL,'a:0:{}','2016-06-17 21:11:53',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(3,23647,'code_n16-contest',1888,1,'CODE_n16 CONTEST','00:00:00','00:00:00',1,'2016-09-20','2016-09-22','https://www.code-n.org/contest.html',0,NULL,'00:00:00',0,0,5,NULL,NULL,'a:0:{}','2016-06-17 22:02:22',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(4,23654,'wordcamp-europe-2016',851,1,'WordCamp Europe 2016','00:00:00','00:00:00',1,'2016-08-04','2016-08-06','https://2016.europe.wordcamp.org/',0,NULL,'00:00:00',0,0,6,NULL,NULL,'a:0:{}','2016-06-19 22:56:57','2016-08-04 21:53:31',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(5,23658,'coldplay-in-london',851,1,'Coldplay in London','18:30:00','22:30:00',0,'2016-08-19','2016-08-19','<h3><a href=\"http://www.axs.com/uk/artists/104084/coldplay-tickets\">Coldplay</a> &amp; Special Guests</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.axs.com/uk/artists/250849/laura-mvula-tickets\">Laura Mvula</a>, George The Poet, <a href=\"http://www.axs.com/uk/artists/1025195/nico-vinz-tickets\">Nico &amp; Vinz</a> Tue, 28 Jun 2016\r\n<h4>Event Info</h4>\r\n<b>Doors Open: </b>18:30 <b>Onsale: </b>Fri, 27 May 2016 - 09:00 BST\r\nAll ticket proceeds to go to Sentebale, registered charity number 1113544\r\nTicket limit: 4\r\nUnder-18s must be accompanied by an adult over 21\r\n\r\nGeneral Admission Ticket Includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General Admission entry through the main gate.</li>\r\n	<li>Access to bars and toilets in the main arena (Please note you will not be permitted to bring any food or beverages into the venue.)</li>\r\n	<li>Opportunity for standing directly in front of the stage. Access may be first come, first served. The Orangery Package Includes:</li>\r\n	<li>Exclusive access to The Kensington Palace Orangery, surrounded by the beautiful gardens in the grounds of Kensington Palace, 1.5 hours ahead of the show (6.30pm arrival, 8pm concert start)</li>\r\n	<li>Exclusive drinks and canapés reception before the show in The Orangery (Please note you will not be permitted to bring any food or beverages into the venue.)</li>\r\n	<li>Access to bars and toilets in the main arena</li>\r\n	<li>Premium View standing area to watch the concert</li>\r\n	<li>Commemorative programme Door Time for Orangery Package holders: 6:00PM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDoor Time for General Admission: 6:30PM Website: <a href=\"http://www.sentebale.org\">www.sentebale.org</a>, Twitter/Instagram: <a href=\"http://www.sentebale.org\">@Sentebale</a> Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.sentebale.org\">SentebaleOfficial</a>',0,NULL,'00:00:00',0,0,7,NULL,NULL,'a:0:{}','2016-06-19 23:09:12','2016-08-04 21:53:53',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(6,23662,'sting-peter-gabriel-in-nyc',1888,1,'Sting & Peter Gabriel Live Tour in NYC','19:00:00','23:00:00',0,'2016-08-22','2016-08-25','<a href=\"https://uploads-demo.getp