:52:22','2016-03-12 11:52:22','','[:en]Disabled: Thoughts against Something/Someone[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20984-revision-v1','','','2016-03-12 19:52:22','2016-03-12 11:52:22','',20984,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20984-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22941,851,'2016-03-12 19:53:16','2016-03-12 11:53:16','','[:en]Disabled: My Thoughts on Something/Someone[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20272-revision-v1','','','2016-03-12 19:53:16','2016-03-12 11:53:16','',20272,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20272-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22942,851,'2016-03-12 19:54:18','2016-03-12 11:54:18','[:en]<h4>Is it free to register in the website?</h4>\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Is it free to use all services from the website, such as posting content, subscribing to newsletter, and others?</h4>\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Do I need to register to use the website?</h4>\r\nTo be able to post content, extract important information, leave your thought about TPP or add comments, yes you need. Just to browse the website there is no need to register.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Why are there Organization and Individual accounts?</h4>\r\nBecause we believe that an organization\'s opinion in regards to TPP might carry more weight than that from an individual, we have split it to make it easy to analyze all information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Is there any difference between an Organization and an Individual account rights?</h4>\r\nThere is only one difference: Organizations can have \'members\' in the website, and each piece of content posted by any member will also appear under the Organization profile page.[:]','[:en]FAQ: User account in RIPESS Asia[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20078-revision-v1','','','2016-03-12 19:54:18','2016-03-12 11:54:18','',20078,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20078-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22943,851,'2016-03-12 19:54:33','2016-03-12 11:54:33','[:en]<h4>Who can add content in TPP Debate?</h4>\r\nAnyone.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Is it free?</h4>\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Do I need to log in to add content?</h4>\r\nYes, only registered users can add content.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Do the users of the website also need to log in to read my content?</h4>\r\nNo, anyone can access the website and read all the content.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Will my content be published immediately?</h4>\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Can I delete content that I have already posted?</h4>\r\nFor the time being this feature is not available in the website, however you can set your post as \'Draft\', and then it will not be online anymore.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>What happens if my content is inappropriate (eg: spam)?</h4>\r\nAnyone can flag any content for being inappropriate, and our admins will take this content offline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Can I share my post with more authors?</h4>\r\nFor \'Thoughts about TPP\' and \'Extracts of important information\', no. For everything else (links, articles, stories, announcements, events) yes. To do so, when creating a new post, on the right side there is a field \'Co-authors\', where you can add more users (either Organizations or Individuals) to own the post. They will both appear as authors and have full editing access.[:]','[:en]FAQ: Adding content in RIPESS Asia[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20076-revision-v1','','','2016-03-12 19:54:33','2016-03-12 11:54:33','',20076,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20076-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22944,851,'2016-03-12 19:54:51','2016-03-12 11:54:51','','[:en]Disabled: Article-related thoughts pro Something/Someone[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20982-revision-v1','','','2016-03-12 19:54:51','2016-03-12 11:54:51','',20982,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20982-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22945,851,'2016-03-12 19:55:05','2016-03-12 11:55:05','','[:en]Disabled: Article-related thoughts neutral to Something/Someone[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20990-revision-v1','','','2