&nbsp;\r\n<h4>What happens if my content is inappropriate (eg: spam)?</h4>\r\nAnyone can flag any content for being inappropriate, and our admins will take this content offline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Can I share my post with more authors?</h4>\r\nFor \'Thoughts about TPP\' and \'Extracts of important information\', no. For everything else (links, articles, stories, announcements, events) yes. To do so, when creating a new post, on the right side there is a field \'Co-authors\', where you can add more users (either Organizations or Individuals) to own the post. They will both appear as authors and have full editing access.[:]','[:en]FAQ: Adding content in TPP Debate[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20076-revision-v1','','','2016-01-18 18:40:45','2016-01-18 10:40:45','',20076,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20076-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22955,851,'2016-03-13 01:15:41','2016-03-12 17:15:41','','[:en]Volunteer[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','22954-revision-v1','','','2016-03-13 01:15:41','2016-03-12 17:15:41','',22954,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/22954-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22954,851,'2016-03-13 01:15:41','2016-03-12 17:15:41','','[:en]Volunteer[:es]Ofrecerme como Voluntario[:zh]当志愿者[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','volunteer','','','2016-03-13 01:15:41','2016-03-12 17:15:41','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/?page_id=22954',0,'page','',0,0),(23540,851,'2016-06-16 13:48:11','2016-06-16 05:48:11','','bullseye','','inherit','closed','closed','','bullseye-2','','','2016-06-16 13:48:11','2016-06-16 05:48:11','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/06/bullseye.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0,0),(23541,851,'2016-06-16 13:51:38','2016-06-16 05:51:38','','aliran.com','','inherit','closed','closed','','aliran-com-2','','','2016-06-16 13:51:38','2016-06-16 05:51:38','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/06/aliran.com_.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0,0),(23347,851,'2016-04-09 17:53:59','2016-04-09 09:53:59','[:en]Welcome to RIPESS Asia! Below, the features you will find in this website, and how to make full use of them.\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-account\">Registering in the website</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-accounttypes\">Account types</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-communities\">Communities</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-content\">Website content</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-typesofcontent\">Types of content</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-contentlinks\">Links</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-extracts\">Extracts of important information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentcreation\">Content creation</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-newpost\">Creating a new post</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-postreferences\">Referencing other posts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-coauthors\">Adding co-authors</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-newextract\">Extracting important information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentmodification\">Content modification</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-editpost\">Editing a post</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-editextract\">Editing an Extract</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentmoderation\">Content moderation</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-flag\">Flagging content as inappropriate</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-notifications\">Notifications</a></strong>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#howtouse-notificationsbadge\">Real time updates</a></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-useractivity\">User activity</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-follow\">Following other users</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-recommend\">Recommending posts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-addingcomments\">Adding comments</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-updownvote\">Voting extracts of important information</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-responseto\">Replying to a post with another post</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-shareandcontact\">Contacting users, Sharing content</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-mentions\">@Mentions</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sendmsg\">Send a message to another user</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sm\">Social media, Share by email</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-embed\">Embed</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-features\">Website features</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-hashtags\">#Hashtags</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-volunteering\">Volunteering</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-lang\">Multiple languages</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-feed\">Content feed</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-search\">Searching, quick access to tags, users\' profiles and content</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-filter\">Filter information tags, categories and others</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-tabs\">Browsing history</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-navigator\">Navigator</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sideinfo\">Side information</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-views\">Multiple view options</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-calendar\">Events calendar</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-stayingconnected\">Staying connected</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-account\">Registering in the website</h2>\r\nAnyone can register for free! Users need to register only to be able to post content on the website; to browse content, there is no need.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-accounttypes\">Account types</h3>\r\nThere are two types of user account:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/create-individual-profile/\">Individual</a> account</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/create-organization-profile/\">Organization</a> account</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23326\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-youraccount.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23326 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-youraccount.jpg\" alt=\"Your account on RIPESS Asia\" width=\"420\" height=\"224\" /></a> Your account on RIPESS Asia[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEach user of the website has a public profile, showing all his/her content: articles, events, etc. Eg: this is <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/leo/\">Leo\'s profile</a>.\r\n\r\nThe difference between Individuals and Organizations, is that Organizations can act as a “community” by having members on the website (see below).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-communities\">Communities</h3>\r\nOrganizations can have members in the website, and all content from their members will also show on the Organization\'s profile.\r\n\r\nEg: RIPESS Asia has many <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/ripess/?tab=members\">members</a>, on <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/ripess/\">its profile page</a> it shows content from all of them.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23330\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-members.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23330\" data-size=\"924x740\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23330\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-members-640x513.jpg\" alt=\"RIPESS Asia\'s members\" width=\"640\" height=\"513\" /></a> RIPESS Asia\'s members[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Users: Joining an organization</h4>\r\nUsers can join organizations in the website on the <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-organizations/\">My Organizations</a> page. Simply type the name of the organization in the input, select it from the dropdown menu, and click on Save:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23333\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-myorganizations.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23333\" data-size=\"878x317\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23333\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-myorganizations-640x231.jpg\" alt=\"My Organizations\" width=\"640\" height=\"231\" /></a> My Organizations[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Organizations: Managing their members</h4>\r\nThe organization manage each member\'s status in the <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-members/\">My Members</a> page:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23332\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mymembers.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23332\" data-size=\"1086x741\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23332\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mymembers-640x437.jpg\" alt=\"My Members\" width=\"640\" height=\"437\" /></a> My Members[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe organization can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accept or reject the user as a member of the Organization. <em>Default: accepted.</em></li>\r\n	<li>Determine if the content posted by the member will also appear under the organization. <em>Default: yes.</em></li>\r\n	<li>Choose what type of member it is: staff, volunteer, student, others. <em>Default: \'member\'.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23331\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-editmembership.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23331\" data-size=\"449x399\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23331\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-editmembership.jpg\" alt=\"Editing a user\'s membership\" width=\"449\" height=\"399\" /></a> Editing a user\'s membership[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-content\">Website content</h2>\r\nRIPESS Asia encourages our community of users to upload and share information about the Social and Solidarity Economy (SSE) from all over Asia.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-typesofcontent\">Types of content</h3>\r\nThe following content types can be created on the website:\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/quick-posts/\">Quick Posts</a></strong>\r\nShort and concise information, it displays directly in the content feed. Ideal for sharing multimedia, such as Youtube videos, images, PDF documents and Powerpoint presentations.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/articles/\">Articles</a></strong>\r\nAny kind of information on SSE in Asia.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/stories/\">Stories</a></strong>\r\nExperiences after contributing to a project or activity.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/projects/\">Projects</a></strong>\r\nWhat is going on in the ground, who is making a difference and how.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/announcements/\">Announcements</a></strong>\r\nRequests for collaboration, employment or internship announcements, press releases, et.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/events/\">Events</a></strong>\r\nAll activities related to SSE: conferences, seminars, workshops, etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-contentlinks\">Links</h3>\r\nAll content types can also be added as “links”, that is, instead of having to copy/paste content from other websites, you can simply embed their link directly in this website.\r\n\r\nThis is particularly useful to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Generate discussions referring to content posted in another website</li>\r\n	<li>Share content directly from an Organization\'s website</li>\r\n	<li>Add events in our <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/calendar/\">Events calendar</a> without the need to ask the authors to do it</li>\r\n	<li>Etc</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23346\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-23346\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2015/12/ripess-link-640x473.jpg\" alt=\"Link to an external webpage\" width=\"640\" height=\"473\" /> Link to an external webpage[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-extracts\">Extracts of important information</h3>\r\nAny user can extract the really important, meaningful bits of information from each post. These extracts will show in the Content feed, alleviating the need for each user to click on each single article to understand what it is about. More than 1 extract can be created per post, and any user can do it, ie its author does not need to be the author of the original post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20832\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extracts.jpg\" data-size=\"713x530\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20832\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extracts-640x476.jpg\" alt=\"Extracts of important information\" width=\"640\" height=\"476\" /></a> Extracts of important information[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentcreation\">Content creation</h2>\r\nThe website is purely crowd-sourced: anyone can post any content on it.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-newpost\">Creating a new post</h3>\r\nTo create any piece of content, simply click on the “+” link on the top navigation bar, and select what type of content you would like to create:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23325\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addpost.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23325 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addpost.jpg\" alt=\"Adding a post on RIPESS Asia\" width=\"420\" height=\"260\" /></a> Adding a post on RIPESS Asia[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThen fill the content in the window that opens. Each content type has its own content fields. For instance, the steps to <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/add-article-link/\">create an article link</a> are:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Copy/paste the link URL</li>\r\n	<li>Input the page title</li>\r\n	<li>Select the categories</li>\r\n	<li>Press Submit</li>\r\n	<li>Voilà! The post will be online immediately!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20834\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-addlink.jpg\" data-size=\"1070x705\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20834\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-addlink-640x422.jpg\" alt=\"Posting a Link\" width=\"640\" height=\"422\" /></a> Posting a Link[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-postreferences\">Referencing other posts</h3>\r\nAnyone has the ability to reply to a post with another post, such as an Article. It is possible to reply to either 1 or more posts. To do so, simply type the name of all articles you wish to reply to, and select them from the suggestions presented:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20829\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"368\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-suggestions.jpg\" data-size=\"368x420\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20829\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-suggestions.jpg\" alt=\"Select the post from the drop-down list\" width=\"368\" height=\"420\" /></a> Select the post from the drop-down list[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20830\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-morethan1.jpg\" data-size=\"317x402\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20830\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-morethan1.jpg\" alt=\"It is possible to reply/reference to more than 1 post\" width=\"317\" height=\"402\" /></a> It is possible to reply/reference to more than 1 post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFinally, these posts will all appear interlinked on the content feed:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20821\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-additionals.jpg\" data-size=\"667x391\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20821\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-additionals-640x375.jpg\" alt=\"All responses/additional posts appear inter-linked\" width=\"640\" height=\"375\" /></a> All responses/additional posts appear inter-linked[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-coauthors\">Adding co-authors</h3>\r\nWhen creating content, users are allowed to select any number of co-authors, which will not only be displayed on the corresponding post, but also will have rights to edit the post. To add co-authors, simply type their name on the “Co-authors” input in box “Meta information”, and select them:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20828\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-coauthors.jpg\" data-size=\"317x339\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20828\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-coauthors.jpg\" alt=\"Adding co-authors\" width=\"317\" height=\"339\" /></a> Adding co-authors[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll co-authors will be shown on the created post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23334\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"522\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-coauthors.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23334\" data-size=\"522x357\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23334\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-coauthors.jpg\" alt=\"Post co-authors\" width=\"522\" height=\"357\" /></a> Post co-authors[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-newextract\">Extracting important information</h3>\r\nIn each post, there is a link “Extract important information”. Simply copy/paste from the original article into the textarea in the opening little window, and then press Submit:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20912\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"516\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractlink.jpg\" data-size=\"516x66\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20912\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractlink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to extract important information from the post\" width=\"516\" height=\"66\" /></a> Link to extract important information from the post[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20840\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"450\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractimportant.jpg\" data-size=\"450x383\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20840\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractimportant.jpg\" alt=\"Extracting important information from a post\" width=\"450\" height=\"383\" /></a> Extracting important information from a post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentmodification\">Content modification</h2>\r\nOn the main navigation (if not visible, click on Toggle navigation button on the top navigation bar to open it on the left side) there is a link <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-content/\">My Content</a>. Click there to see a list of all your posts.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23337\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"353\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mainmenu.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23337\" data-size=\"353x755\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23337\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mainmenu.jpg\" alt=\"Main menu\" width=\"353\" height=\"755\" /></a> Main menu[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-editpost\">Editing a post</h3>\r\nBelow each entry, there is a button \"Edit\", click on it to edit your post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20907\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-mycontent.jpg\" data-size=\"777x382\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20907\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-mycontent-640x315.jpg\" alt=\"My Content\" width=\"640\" height=\"315\" /></a> My Content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-editextract\">Editing an Extract</h3>\r\nOn the main navigation there is a link <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-extracts/\">My Extracts</a>. Click there to see a list of all your extracts. Below each entry, there is a button \"Edit\", click on it to edit it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentmoderation\">Content moderation</h2>\r\nWe do not modify the content posted by any user (unless it has formatting problems, on which case we fix these). However, if the content does not adhere to our <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/content-guidelines/\">content guidelines</a> our admins will take it offline.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-flag\">Flagging content as inappropriate</h3>\r\nUsers of the website are encouraged to flag any piece of content as inappropriate, and we will analyze the case and take action if needed.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20915\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-flag.jpg\" data-size=\"710x242\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20915\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-flag-640x218.jpg\" alt=\"Link to flag a post\" width=\"640\" height=\"218\" /></a> Link to flag a post[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20842\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-inappropriate.jpg\" data-size=\"449x380\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20842\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-inappropriate.jpg\" alt=\"Content can be flagged as inappropriate by our users\" width=\"449\" height=\"380\" /></a> Content can be flagged as inappropriate by our users[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-notifications\">Notifications</h2>\r\nUpon logging in, users will receive <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/notifications/\">notifications</a> with the activity from their user network, which is comprised of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All followed users</li>\r\n	<li>All members of the same organizations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUsers get the following notifications:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General notifications, such as important announcements by RIPESS Asia</li>\r\n	<li>Actions requested from them, such as updating their profile if needed</li>\r\n	<li>When they are followed by someone else, or someone from their network follows another user or joins an organization</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone added a comment on, or created a post related to, the user\'s post</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone replied to a comment by the user</li>\r\n	<li>Someone from their network creates a new post, recommends a post, adds a comment, follows another user, or joins an organization</li>\r\n	<li>For Organizations: when they get a new member</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23329\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-notifications.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23329\" data-size=\"420x528\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23329\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-notifications.jpg\" alt=\"User notifications\" width=\"420\" height=\"528\" /></a> User notifications[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-notificationsbadge\">Real time updates</h3>\r\nWhen logged in, users will receive notifications from events happening on real time. For this, a badge announcing the new notifications wil appear: <img src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2015/12/ripess-notificationsbadge.jpg\" alt=\"ripess-notificationsbadge\" width=\"116\" height=\"44\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23345\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-useractivity\">User activity</h2>\r\nThe website has implemented several feedback mechanisms for our community of users to engage in a conversation.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-follow\">Following other users</h3>\r\nWhen following a user, you will receive notifications following this user\'s activity, such as recommending content, posting a new article, comment, etc:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20827\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"315\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-follow.jpg\" data-size=\"315x182\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20827\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-follow.jpg\" alt=\"Follow users and get notifications following their activity\" width=\"315\" height=\"182\" /></a> Follow users and get notifications following their activity[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-recommend\">Recommending posts</h3>\r\nUsers can share their recommendations with their followers, and members of the same organizations:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20826\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-recommend.jpg\" data-size=\"659x270\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20826\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-recommend-640x262.jpg\" alt=\"Recommend posts, your followers will get a notification\" width=\"640\" height=\"262\" /></a> Recommend posts, your followers will get a notification[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-addingcomments\">Adding comments</h3>\r\nOn any post, simply click on \"Write a comment\" to add a comment, or \"Reply\" to reply to any comment. Comments allow: formatting, such as bold fonts, adding colors, etc; embedding media, such as uploading images or documents or embedding Youtube videos; @mentions, to tag a particular user on the comment; and #hashtags.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23320\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-23320\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addingcomments-640x343.png\" alt=\"Adding comments\" width=\"640\" height=\"343\" /> Adding comments[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-updownvote\">Voting extracts of important information</h3>\r\nUsers can vote if an extract is important or not.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20825\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"633\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-important.jpg\" data-size=\"633x189\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20825\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-important.jpg\" alt=\"Up-vote / Down-vote an Extract: “Is it important?”\" width=\"633\" height=\"189\" /></a> Up-vote / Down-vote an Extract: “Is it important?”[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-responseto\">Replying to a post with another post</h3>\r\nTo reply to a post with another post, at the end of it there is a link: “Add response/additional”, with all content types showing in a drop-down menu:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20913\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"519\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-responseto.jpg\" data-size=\"519x188\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20913\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-responseto.jpg\" alt=\"Reply to any post with another post\" width=\"519\" height=\"188\" /></a> Reply to any post with another post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUpon clicking the corresponding link, such as “Article”, it will open the “Add Article” page, with the original article already pre-selected under field “In response/as an addition to” in box “Meta information”:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20831\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response.jpg\" data-size=\"317x304\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20831\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response.jpg\" alt=\"Anyone can reply to the post author with a article, announcement, etc\" width=\"317\" height=\"304\" /></a> Anyone can reply to the post author with a article, announcement, etc[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-shareandcontact\">Contacting users, Sharing content</h2>\r\nUsers can interact with each other, all content in the website can be easily shared through different means.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-mentions\">@Mentions</h3>\r\nWhen creating a post or adding a comment, you can mention any user, and this person will receive a notification and an email. Simply type “@” and then start typing the name of the person, and select him/her from the dropdown list:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23249\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/03/mentions.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23249 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/03/mentions.jpg\" alt=\"@Mentions\" width=\"300\" height=\"218\" /></a> @Mentions[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sendmsg\">Send a message to another user</h3>\r\nIf you need to contact any user on our website, you can do so. Simply click on the \"Send message\" button, type your message on the new window, and click \"Send\". The user will get your message by email.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20906\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"473\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-sendmessage.jpg\" data-size=\"473x381\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20906\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-sendmessage.jpg\" alt=\"Send a message to any user\" width=\"473\" height=\"381\" /></a> Send a message to any user[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sm\">Social media, Share by email</h3>\r\nShare on Facebook, Twitter, or by email:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20818\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-postoptions.jpg\" data-size=\"709x230\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20818\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-postoptions-640x208.jpg\" alt=\"Share posts on Facebook, Twitter or by email\" width=\"640\" height=\"208\" /></a> Share posts on Facebook, Twitter or by email[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-embed\">Embed</h3>\r\nAll content in the website can be easily embedded on your own website:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20911\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embedlink.jpg\" data-size=\"713x268\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20911\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embedlink-640x241.jpg\" alt=\"Link to embed content\" width=\"640\" height=\"241\" /></a> Link to embed content[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20817\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"599\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embed.jpg\" data-size=\"599x511\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20817\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embed.jpg\" alt=\"Embed any content on your own website\" width=\"599\" height=\"511\" /></a> Embed any content on your own website[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-features\">Website features</h2>\r\nThe features below are thought for giving the users endless possibilities in exploring all the content in the website, from accessing it in different languages, to filtering, to keeping all open pages readily accessible.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-hashtags\">#Hashtags</h3>\r\nWhen creating a post or adding a comment, you can add a Twitter-like hashtag. Simply type # and the topic, and all posts/comments can be grouped by hashtag/topic. #ripessasia #websitefeatures\r\n\r\nTo see a list of all existing hashtags, simply start typing the #hashtag in your post or comment, and a list will appear:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23335\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-hashtag.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23335\" data-size=\"449x396\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23335\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-hashtag.jpg\" alt=\"Adding a #hashtag\" width=\"449\" height=\"396\" /></a> Adding a #hashtag[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-volunteering\">Volunteering</h3>\r\nIn sections <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/projects/\">Projects</a>, <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/announcements/\">Announcements</a> and <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/events/\">Events</a>, the author of the post can invite volunteers to participate in their causes:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23327\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"522\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-clicktovolunteer.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23327\" data-size=\"522x402\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23327\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-clicktovolunteer.jpg\" alt=\"Click to Volunteer\" width=\"522\" height=\"402\" /></a> Click to Volunteer[/caption]\r\n\r\nUpon submitting the form, the organizers will get the volunteer\'s information and contact details:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23328\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-volunteer.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23328\" data-size=\"420x385\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23328\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-volunteer.jpg\" alt=\"Volunteer\'s data is sent to the organizers\" width=\"420\" height=\"385\" /></a> Volunteer\'s data is sent to the organizers[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-lang\">Multiple languages</h3>\r\nThe website frame has been translated to 4 languages: English, Malay, Tamil and Chinese (due to constant website updates, the translations might not be 100% complete or accurate). To access these, the links are visible on the homepage:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23336\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"612\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-languages.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23336\" data-size=\"612x43\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23336\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-languages.jpg\" alt=\"Multiple languages\" width=\"612\" height=\"43\" /></a> Multiple languages[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-feed\">Content feed</h3>\r\nThe homepage of the website is already a feed of all SSE-related content. Keep scrolling down, keep reading all content posted by all our users.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-search\">Searching, quick access to tags, users\' profiles and content</h3>\r\nOn the top navigation bar, there is a search input. Typing in allows to select the users\' profile, post or tag very quickly, or perform a search of users or content on the website:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-search.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23340\" data-size=\"691x576\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23340\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-search-640x533.jpg\" alt=\"Searching / quick access to tags, users and content\" width=\"640\" height=\"533\" /></a> Searching / quick access to tags, users and content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-filter\">Filter information tags, categories and others</h3>\r\nSince when creating any post the user can select tags, categories it applies to, and other metadata, then all content can be filtered using these parameters:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-filtering.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23341\" data-size=\"863x450\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23341\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-filtering-640x334.jpg\" alt=\"Fiterling content\" width=\"640\" height=\"334\" /></a> Fiterling content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-tabs\">Browsing history</h3>\r\nAnytime you open any page in the website, a tab to access it again will be created. To access all open pages, click on the timer icon on the top navigation bar (with title “Toggle Browsing History”) to see all tabs. Then, clicking on each tab will take you back to that page:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20848\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-tabs.jpg\" data-size=\"1093x80\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20848\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-tabs-640x47.jpg\" alt=\"Browsing history: all tabs with open pages\" width=\"640\" height=\"47\" /></a> Browsing history: all tabs with open pages[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-navigator\">Navigator</h3>\r\nThe navigator is a way to browse all content on the website, allowing the user to keep open and visible the list of posts to browse. All sections on the website can be opened in the Navigator. To use it, toggle open the navigation menu by clicking on the menu icon, on the top navigation bar, and then on each section link there is a right arrow with tooltip text \"Navigate\". Simply click there, and a left panel, containing all posts for that section, will open on the left side. Clicking on each of the posts will not close the Navigator.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20909\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"291\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigatelink.jpg\" data-size=\"291x132\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20909\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigatelink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to open the Navigator for a given section\" width=\"291\" height=\"132\" /></a> Link to open the Navigator for a given section[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20908\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"329\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigator.jpg\" data-size=\"329x885\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20908\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigator.jpg\" alt=\"Navigator\" width=\"329\" height=\"885\" /></a> Navigator[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sideinfo\">Side information</h3>\r\nEach post\'s meta-information shows on top of each post, and also on the Side information panel. To open it, on the top right corner of the post, there is an \"Options\" button, with a drop-down menu. On this menu, click on \"Information\", and the Side information panel will appear from the right side.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20919\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"164\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-informationlink.jpg\" data-size=\"164x118\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20919\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-informationlink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to open the post information\" width=\"164\" height=\"118\" /></a> Link to open the post information[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20918\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"295\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-information.jpg\" data-size=\"295x837\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20918\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-information.jpg\" alt=\"Post information\" width=\"295\" height=\"837\" /></a> Post information[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-views\">Multiple view options</h3>\r\nThere are several ways to browse the Content feed:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Full view</li>\r\n	<li>Details (this is the default view)</li>\r\n	<li>List</li>\r\n	<li>Thumbnail</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, events and users have an additional view:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20820\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventsmap.jpg\" data-size=\"1057x517\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20820\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventsmap-640x313.jpg\" alt=\"Events Map view\" width=\"640\" height=\"313\" /></a> Events Map view[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou can change the default view on the Settings: click on the right-most element on the top navigation bar, and select your preferred option:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20822\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-settings.jpg\" data-size=\"899x322\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20822\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-settings-640x229.jpg\" alt=\"Website settings\" width=\"640\" height=\"229\" /></a> Website settings[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-calendar\">Events calendar</h3>\r\nAll events can be visualized in a lovely <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/calendar/\">Events Calendar</a>:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20819\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventscalendar.jpg\" data-size=\"1057x517\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20819\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventscalendar-640x313.jpg\" alt=\"Events Calendar\" width=\"640\" height=\"313\" /></a> Events Calendar[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-stayingconnected\">Staying connected</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/invite-users/\">Invite your friends to join RIPESS Asia!</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/newsletter/\">Subscribe to RIPESS Asia\'s newsletter campaigns</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/contact-us/\">Contact us</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:]','[:en]How to use the website[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20810-revision-v1','','','2016-04-09 17:53:59','2016-04-09 09:53:59','',20810,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20810-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22444,851,'2016-02-17 20:14:25','2016-02-17 12:14:25','[:en]<h3>KiniTV: <a href=\"http://www.kinitv.com/video/27716O8\">Join the TPP conversation at TPPDebate.org</a></h3>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qh-RTj0XlGM\r\n\r\nThe Malaysia Environmental Sustainability Youth Movements has launched a website at TPPDebate.org as a platform for Malaysians of all ages, colour and creed to voice their opinions on the Trans-Pacific Partnership Act (TPPA), whether they are supportive or against the act.\r\n\r\nAccording to the project administrator Leonardo Losoviz, the information gathered from this project will be handed over to some members of parliament prior to the special sitting later this month to address the controversial free trade agreement.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Nanyang Siang Pau 南洋商报：<a href=\"http://www.nanyang.com/node/739410?tid=460\">社运分子创设‧供各造表态 TPPDebate.org针砭跨协</a></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/wansaiful-azlan.jpg\" data-size=\"1574x1082\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-20778\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/wansaiful-azlan-225x155.jpg\" alt=\"wansaiful-azlan\" width=\"225\" height=\"155\" /></a>（吉隆坡16日讯）随着跨太平洋伙伴关系协定（TPPA）内容于上月5日公开后，我国是否要签署跨协成关注课题，为了让人民有反映看法和意见的平台，社运分子设立TPPDebate.org，让各组织和人民都能表达各自立场。\r\n\r\n该网站的设立者与2013年设立商讨环境课题的MESYM.com网站团队相同，希望通过该网站的设立，让组织和个人都能发表立场，推动人们就跨协利弊辩论和对谈，同时收集赞同或反对的数据。\r\n<a title=\"網站設平台‧讓網民辯論TPP\" href=\"http://www.nanyang.com/node/739410?tid=460\">Read full article</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>The Edge TV: <a href=\"http://www.theedgemarkets.com/my/video-photo/the-edge-tv/248934\">Web portal launched to promote public debate about the TPP</a></h3>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/gQl5c-IcTPY\r\n\r\nIn the run up to debate about Trans-Pacific Partnership in parliament in January, the Malaysia Environmental Sustainability Youth Movement has launched a web platform, TPPDebate.org to encourage public debate about TPP. An anti-TPPA movement says issues affecting public interest within the TPP agreement text should be further discussed. However, Institute for Democracy and Economic Affairs says Malaysians should not reject it just because of certain contents within the text.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Web portal launched to promote public debate about the TPP\" href=\"http://www.theedgemarkets.com/my/video-photo/the-edge-tv/248934\">Read full article</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Sinchew Daily 星洲日报：<a href=\"http://news.sinchew.com.my/node/457627?tid=1\">網站設平台‧讓網民辯論TPP</a></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/sinchew.leo_.jpg\" data-size=\"614x409\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-20750\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/sinchew.leo_-225x150.jpg\" alt=\"sinchew.leo\" width=\"225\" height=\"150\" /></a>（吉隆坡16日訊）由非營利單位設立的跨太平洋夥伴關係（TPP）協議辯論平台（TPPDebate.com）今日正式推介，提供平台讓網民留言辯論TPP課題。\r\n\r\n該網頁負責人里奧納多表示，每一位用戶都可以在網頁上針對TPP課題發表留言，並選擇“支持”、“中立”及“反對”TPP的立場，有關立場事後可以更改。\r\n\r\n他說，用戶可以選擇作為個人用戶或團體代表。\r\n<a title=\"網站設平台‧讓網民辯論TPP\" href=\"http://news.sinchew.com.my/node/457627?tid=1\">Read full article</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Anadolu Agency (Turkey): <a href=\"http://aa.com.tr/en/todays-headlines/malaysians-launch-trans-pacific-pact-debate-website/491809\">Malaysians launch Trans-Pacific pact debate website</a></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/anadolupic.jpg\" data-size=\"863x486\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-20783\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/anadolupic-225x127.jpg\" alt=\"anadolupic\" width=\"225\" height=\"127\" /></a><em>Public can voice opinions, concerns on platform visible to lawmakers before regional trade pact presented to parliament</em>\r\n\r\nThe launch of TPPDebate.org on Wednesday came five weeks before the final agreement – a regional trade pact with the United States – is presented to Malaysia’s parliament to win the approval of lawmakers before its signing.\r\n\r\nDr. Jun-E Tan, the website\'s developer, told a media briefing Wednesday that TPPDebate.org provides a neutral ground for both sides of the debate to raise arguments backed by facts and figures on how Malaysia and its citizens will be affected by the TPP.\r\n<a title=\"Malaysians launch Trans-Pacific pact debate website\" href=\"http://aa.com.tr/en/todays-headlines/malaysians-launch-trans-pacific-pact-debate-website/491809\">Read full article</a>.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Malaysiakini: <a title=\"Confused about TPPA? Meet the couple who try to cut the clutter\" href=\"http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/322252\">Confused about TPPA? Meet the couple who try to cut the clutter\r\n</a></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/leo-jun-e-msiakini.png\" data-size=\"800x480\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-20689\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/04/leo-jun-e-msiakini-225x135.png\" alt=\"leo-jun-e-msiakini\" width=\"225\" height=\"135\" /></a>Are you confused about the Trans-Pacific Partnership Agreement (TPPA)? Can\'t make heads or tails out of the intimidating 6,350-page document?\r\n\r\nA husband-and-wife team found themselves in this situation about a month ago, and decided to do something about it.\r\n<a title=\"Confused about TPPA? Meet the couple who try to cut the clutter\" href=\"http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/322252\">Read full article</a>.[:]','[:en]TPP Debate in the Media[:ms]TPP Debate dalam Media[:ta]ஊடகம் மூலம் TPP Debate[:zh]TPP Debate在媒体[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','18866-revision-v1','','','2016-02-17 20:14:25','2016-02-17 12:14:25','',18866,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/18866-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(22459,851,'2016-03-10 15:55:30','2016-03-10 07:55:30','[:en]PoP allows our community of users to contribute different kinds of content, including articles, projects, stories, events, and others. Our community is encouraged to flag unsuitable content, after which it will be removed by the website admins. The following are our content guidelines:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Inappropriate content</strong>:\r\nHate speech, cyber-bulling, pornographic material, and any type of bigotry are not allowed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Unrelated content:</strong>\r\nRIPESS Asia is about sharing information on SSE, ie Social and Solidarity Economy. Please stick to posting only this kind of information.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Promotional content</strong>:\r\nThis is accepted as long as it is related to SSE-related issues, however the information in the article must be valuable to our community, it cannot be just about selling a product or promoting a brand.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Privacy</strong>:\r\nPublicizing other people’s private information is not allowed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Intellectual property</strong>:\r\nPlease refrain from copy/pasting content from other websites, unless you are the owner of the content.</li>\r\n</ul>[:es]PoP permite a nuestra comunidad de usuarios contribuir diferentes tipos de contenido, incluyendo artículos, proyectos, historias, eventos y otros. Animamos a la comunidad a marcar aquél contenido que no sea apropiado, alertando a los administradores de sitios web para que puedan removerlo. Las siguientes son las reglas de publicación de contenido:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Contenido inapropiado:</strong>\r\nLas expresiones de odio, ciberacoso, material pornográfico, y cualquier tipo de intolerancia no están permitidos.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>contenido no relacionado: </strong>\r\nPor favor, adhiéranse a publicar información sólamente relacionado al tópico de este sitio web.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Contenido promocional:</strong>\r\nEsto se acepta siempre y cuando esté relacionado con el tópico del sitio web, sin embargo, la información en el artículo debe ser valioso para nuestra comunidad, no puede ser sólo para vender un producto o promoción de una marca.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Privacidad:</strong>\r\nNo se permite dar a conocer información privada de otras personas.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Propiedad intelectual </strong>:\r\nPor favor, abstenerse de copiar/pegar contenido de otros sitios web, a menos que usted sea el propietario del contenido.</li>\r\n</ul>[:]','[:en]Content guidelines[:es]Reglas de publicación de contenido[:zh]内容指南[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','content-guidelines','','','2016-06-13 23:45:58','2016-06-13 15:45:58','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/?page_id=22459',0,'page','',0,0),(22460,851,'2016-03-10 15:55:30','2016-03-10 07:55:30','[:en]TPP Debate allows our community of users to contribute different kinds of content, including articles, projects, stories, events, thoughts on TPP, and others. Our community is encouraged to flag unsuitable content, after which it will be removed by the website admins. The following are our content guidelines:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Inappropriate content</strong>:\r\nHate speech, cyber-bulling, pornographic material, and any type of bigotry are not allowed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Unrelated content:</strong>\r\nTPP Debate is about debating the TPP. Please stick to posting only TPP-related information.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Promotional content</strong>:\r\nThis is accepted as long as it is related to environmental issues, however the information in the article must be valuable to our community, it cannot be just about selling a product or promoting a brand.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Privacy</strong>:\r\nPublicizing other people’s private information is not allowed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Intellectual property</strong>:\r\nPlease refrain from copy/pasting content from other websites, unless you are the owner of the content.</li>\r\n</ul>[:]','[:en]Content guidelines[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','22459-revision-v1','','','2016-03-10 15:55:30','2016-03-10 07:55:30','',22459,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/22459-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(23350,851,'2016-04-10 13:02:51','2016-04-10 05:02:51','[:en]Welcome to RIPESS Asia! Below, the features you will find in this website, and how to make full use of them.\r\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-account\">Registering in the website</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-accounttypes\">Account types</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-communities\">Communities</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-content\">Website content</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-typesofcontent\">Types of content</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-contentlinks\">Links</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-extracts\">Extracts of important information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentcreation\">Content creation</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-newpost\">Creating a new post</a>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#howtouse-postreferences\">Referencing other posts</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"#howtouse-coauthors\">Adding co-authors</a></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-newextract\">Extracting important information</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentmodification\">Content modification</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-editpost\">Editing a post</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-editextract\">Editing an Extract</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-contentmoderation\">Content moderation</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-flag\">Flagging content as inappropriate</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-notifications\">Notifications</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-notificationsbadge\">Real time updates</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-useractivity\">User activity</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-follow\">Following other users</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-recommend\">Recommending posts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-addingcomments\">Adding comments</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-updownvote\">Voting extracts of important information</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-responseto\">Replying to a post with another post</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-shareandcontact\">Contacting users, Sharing content</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-mentions\">@Mentions</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sendmsg\">Send a message to another user</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sm\">Social media, Share by email</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-embed\">Embed</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"#howtouse-features\">Website features</a></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-hashtags\">#Hashtags</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-volunteering\">Volunteering</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-lang\">Multiple languages</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-feed\">Content feed</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-search\">Searching, quick access to tags, users\' profiles and content</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-filter\">Filter information tags, categories and others</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-tabs\">Browsing history</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-navigator\">Navigator</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-sideinfo\">Side information</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-views\">Multiple view options</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-calendar\">Events calendar</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#howtouse-stayingconnected\">Staying connected</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-account\">Registering in the website</h2>\r\nAnyone can register for free! Users need to register only to be able to post content on the website; to browse content, there is no need.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-accounttypes\">Account types</h3>\r\nThere are two types of user account:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/create-individual-profile/\">Individual</a> account</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/create-organization-profile/\">Organization</a> account</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23326\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-youraccount.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23326 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-youraccount.jpg\" alt=\"Your account on RIPESS Asia\" width=\"420\" height=\"224\" /></a> Your account on RIPESS Asia[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEach user of the website has a public profile, showing all his/her content: articles, events, etc. Eg: this is <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/leo/\">Leo\'s profile</a>.\r\n\r\nThe difference between Individuals and Organizations, is that Organizations can act as a “community” by having members on the website (see below).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-communities\">Communities</h3>\r\nOrganizations can have members in the website, and all content from their members will also show on the Organization\'s profile.\r\n\r\nEg: RIPESS Asia has many <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/ripess/?tab=members\">members</a>, on <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/u/ripess/\">its profile page</a> it shows content from all of them.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23330\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-members.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23330\" data-size=\"924x740\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23330\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-members-640x513.jpg\" alt=\"RIPESS Asia\'s members\" width=\"640\" height=\"513\" /></a> RIPESS Asia\'s members[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Users: Joining an organization</h4>\r\nUsers can join organizations in the website on the <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-organizations/\">My Organizations</a> page. Simply type the name of the organization in the input, select it from the dropdown menu, and click on Save:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23333\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-myorganizations.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23333\" data-size=\"878x317\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23333\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-myorganizations-640x231.jpg\" alt=\"My Organizations\" width=\"640\" height=\"231\" /></a> My Organizations[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Organizations: Managing their members</h4>\r\nThe organization manage each member\'s status in the <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-members/\">My Members</a> page:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23332\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mymembers.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23332\" data-size=\"1086x741\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23332\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mymembers-640x437.jpg\" alt=\"My Members\" width=\"640\" height=\"437\" /></a> My Members[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe organization can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accept or reject the user as a member of the Organization. <em>Default: accepted.</em></li>\r\n	<li>Determine if the content posted by the member will also appear under the organization. <em>Default: yes.</em></li>\r\n	<li>Choose what type of member it is: staff, volunteer, student, others. <em>Default: \'member\'.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23331\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-editmembership.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23331\" data-size=\"449x399\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23331\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-editmembership.jpg\" alt=\"Editing a user\'s membership\" width=\"449\" height=\"399\" /></a> Editing a user\'s membership[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-content\">Website content</h2>\r\nRIPESS Asia encourages our community of users to upload and share information about the Social and Solidarity Economy (SSE) from all over Asia.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-typesofcontent\">Types of content</h3>\r\nThe following content types can be created on the website:\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/quick-posts/\">Quick Posts</a></strong>\r\nShort and concise information, it displays directly in the content feed. Ideal for sharing multimedia, such as Youtube videos, images, PDF documents and Powerpoint presentations.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/articles/\">Articles</a></strong>\r\nAny kind of information on SSE in Asia.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/stories/\">Stories</a></strong>\r\nExperiences after contributing to a project or activity.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/projects/\">Projects</a></strong>\r\nWhat is going on in the ground, who is making a difference and how.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/announcements/\">Announcements</a></strong>\r\nRequests for collaboration, employment or internship announcements, press releases, et.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/events/\">Events</a></strong>\r\nAll activities related to SSE: conferences, seminars, workshops, etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-contentlinks\">Links</h3>\r\nAll content types can also be added as “links”, that is, instead of having to copy/paste content from other websites, you can simply embed their link directly in this website.\r\n\r\nThis is particularly useful to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Generate discussions referring to content posted in another website</li>\r\n	<li>Share content directly from an Organization\'s website</li>\r\n	<li>Add events in our <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/calendar/\">Events calendar</a> without the need to ask the authors to do it</li>\r\n	<li>Etc</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23346\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-23346\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2015/12/ripess-link-640x473.jpg\" alt=\"Link to an external webpage\" width=\"640\" height=\"473\" /> Link to an external webpage[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-extracts\">Extracts of important information</h3>\r\nAny user can extract the really important, meaningful bits of information from each post. These extracts will show in the Content feed, alleviating the need for each user to click on each single article to understand what it is about. More than 1 extract can be created per post, and any user can do it, ie its author does not need to be the author of the original post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20832\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extracts.jpg\" data-size=\"713x530\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20832\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extracts-640x476.jpg\" alt=\"Extracts of important information\" width=\"640\" height=\"476\" /></a> Extracts of important information[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentcreation\">Content creation</h2>\r\nThe website is purely crowd-sourced: anyone can post any content on it.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-newpost\">Creating a new post</h3>\r\nTo create any piece of content, simply click on the “+” link on the top navigation bar, and select what type of content you would like to create:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23325\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addpost.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23325 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addpost.jpg\" alt=\"Adding a post on RIPESS Asia\" width=\"420\" height=\"260\" /></a> Adding a post on RIPESS Asia[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThen fill the content in the window that opens. Each content type has its own content fields. For instance, the steps to <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/add-article-link/\">create an article link</a> are:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Copy/paste the link URL</li>\r\n	<li>Input the page title</li>\r\n	<li>Select the categories</li>\r\n	<li>Press Submit</li>\r\n	<li>Voilà! The post will be online immediately!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20834\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-addlink.jpg\" data-size=\"1070x705\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20834\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-addlink-640x422.jpg\" alt=\"Posting a Link\" width=\"640\" height=\"422\" /></a> Posting a Link[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4 id=\"howtouse-postreferences\">Referencing other posts</h4>\r\nAnyone has the ability to reply to a post with another post, such as an Article. It is possible to reply to either 1 or more posts. To do so, simply type the name of all articles you wish to reply to, and select them from the suggestions presented:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20829\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"368\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-suggestions.jpg\" data-size=\"368x420\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20829\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-suggestions.jpg\" alt=\"Select the post from the drop-down list\" width=\"368\" height=\"420\" /></a> Select the post from the drop-down list[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20830\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-morethan1.jpg\" data-size=\"317x402\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20830\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response-morethan1.jpg\" alt=\"It is possible to reply/reference to more than 1 post\" width=\"317\" height=\"402\" /></a> It is possible to reply/reference to more than 1 post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFinally, these posts will all appear interlinked on the content feed:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20821\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-additionals.jpg\" data-size=\"667x391\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20821\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-additionals-640x375.jpg\" alt=\"All responses/additional posts appear inter-linked\" width=\"640\" height=\"375\" /></a> All responses/additional posts appear inter-linked[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4 id=\"howtouse-coauthors\">Adding co-authors</h4>\r\nWhen creating content, users are allowed to select any number of co-authors, which will not only be displayed on the corresponding post, but also will have rights to edit the post. To add co-authors, simply type their name on the “Co-authors” input in box “Meta information”, and select them:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20828\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-coauthors.jpg\" data-size=\"317x339\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20828\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-coauthors.jpg\" alt=\"Adding co-authors\" width=\"317\" height=\"339\" /></a> Adding co-authors[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll co-authors will be shown on the created post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23334\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"522\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-coauthors.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23334\" data-size=\"522x357\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23334\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-coauthors.jpg\" alt=\"Post co-authors\" width=\"522\" height=\"357\" /></a> Post co-authors[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-newextract\">Extracting important information</h3>\r\nIn each post, there is a link “Extract important information”. Simply copy/paste from the original article into the textarea in the opening little window, and then press Submit:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20912\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"516\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractlink.jpg\" data-size=\"516x66\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20912\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractlink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to extract important information from the post\" width=\"516\" height=\"66\" /></a> Link to extract important information from the post[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20840\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"450\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractimportant.jpg\" data-size=\"450x383\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20840\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-extractimportant.jpg\" alt=\"Extracting important information from a post\" width=\"450\" height=\"383\" /></a> Extracting important information from a post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentmodification\">Content modification</h2>\r\nOn the main navigation (if not visible, click on Toggle navigation button on the top navigation bar to open it on the left side) there is a link <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-content/\">My Content</a>. Click there to see a list of all your posts.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23337\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"353\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mainmenu.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23337\" data-size=\"353x755\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23337\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-mainmenu.jpg\" alt=\"Main menu\" width=\"353\" height=\"755\" /></a> Main menu[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-editpost\">Editing a post</h3>\r\nBelow each entry, there is a button \"Edit\", click on it to edit your post:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20907\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-mycontent.jpg\" data-size=\"777x382\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20907\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-mycontent-640x315.jpg\" alt=\"My Content\" width=\"640\" height=\"315\" /></a> My Content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-editextract\">Editing an Extract</h3>\r\nOn the main navigation there is a link <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/my-extracts/\">My Extracts</a>. Click there to see a list of all your extracts. Below each entry, there is a button \"Edit\", click on it to edit it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-contentmoderation\">Content moderation</h2>\r\nWe do not modify the content posted by any user (unless it has formatting problems, on which case we fix these). However, if the content does not adhere to our <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/content-guidelines/\">content guidelines</a> our admins will take it offline.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-flag\">Flagging content as inappropriate</h3>\r\nUsers of the website are encouraged to flag any piece of content as inappropriate, and we will analyze the case and take action if needed.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20915\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-flag.jpg\" data-size=\"710x242\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20915\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-flag-640x218.jpg\" alt=\"Link to flag a post\" width=\"640\" height=\"218\" /></a> Link to flag a post[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20842\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-inappropriate.jpg\" data-size=\"449x380\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20842\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-inappropriate.jpg\" alt=\"Content can be flagged as inappropriate by our users\" width=\"449\" height=\"380\" /></a> Content can be flagged as inappropriate by our users[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-notifications\">Notifications</h2>\r\nUpon logging in, users will receive <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/notifications/\">notifications</a> with the activity from their user network, which is comprised of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All followed users</li>\r\n	<li>All members of the same organizations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUsers get the following notifications:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General notifications, such as important announcements by RIPESS Asia</li>\r\n	<li>Actions requested from them, such as updating their profile if needed</li>\r\n	<li>When they are followed by someone else, or someone from their network follows another user or joins an organization</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone added a comment on, or created a post related to, the user\'s post</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone replied to a comment by the user</li>\r\n	<li>Someone from their network creates a new post, recommends a post, adds a comment, follows another user, or joins an organization</li>\r\n	<li>For Organizations: when they get a new member</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23329\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-notifications.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23329\" data-size=\"420x528\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23329\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-notifications.jpg\" alt=\"User notifications\" width=\"420\" height=\"528\" /></a> User notifications[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-notificationsbadge\">Real time updates</h3>\r\nWhen logged in, users will receive notifications from events happening on real time. For this, a badge announcing the new notifications wil appear: <img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23345\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2015/12/ripess-notificationsbadge.jpg\" alt=\"ripess-notificationsbadge\" width=\"116\" height=\"44\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-useractivity\">User activity</h2>\r\nThe website has implemented several feedback mechanisms for our community of users to engage in a conversation.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-follow\">Following other users</h3>\r\nWhen following a user, you will receive notifications following this user\'s activity, such as recommending content, posting a new article, comment, etc:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20827\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"315\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-follow.jpg\" data-size=\"315x182\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20827\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-follow.jpg\" alt=\"Follow users and get notifications following their activity\" width=\"315\" height=\"182\" /></a> Follow users and get notifications following their activity[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-recommend\">Recommending posts</h3>\r\nUsers can share their recommendations with their followers, and members of the same organizations:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20826\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-recommend.jpg\" data-size=\"659x270\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20826\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-recommend-640x262.jpg\" alt=\"Recommend posts, your followers will get a notification\" width=\"640\" height=\"262\" /></a> Recommend posts, your followers will get a notification[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-addingcomments\">Adding comments</h3>\r\nOn any post, simply click on \"Write a comment\" to add a comment, or \"Reply\" to reply to any comment. Comments allow: formatting, such as bold fonts, adding colors, etc; embedding media, such as uploading images or documents or embedding Youtube videos; @mentions, to tag a particular user on the comment; and #hashtags.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23320\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-23320\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-addingcomments-640x343.png\" alt=\"Adding comments\" width=\"640\" height=\"343\" /> Adding comments[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-updownvote\">Voting extracts of important information</h3>\r\nUsers can vote if an extract is important or not.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20825\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"633\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-important.jpg\" data-size=\"633x189\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20825\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-important.jpg\" alt=\"Up-vote / Down-vote an Extract: “Is it important?”\" width=\"633\" height=\"189\" /></a> Up-vote / Down-vote an Extract: “Is it important?”[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-responseto\">Replying to a post with another post</h3>\r\nTo reply to a post with another post, at the end of it there is a link: “Add response/additional”, with all content types showing in a drop-down menu:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20913\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"519\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-responseto.jpg\" data-size=\"519x188\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20913\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-responseto.jpg\" alt=\"Reply to any post with another post\" width=\"519\" height=\"188\" /></a> Reply to any post with another post[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUpon clicking the corresponding link, such as “Article”, it will open the “Add Article” page, with the original article already pre-selected under field “In response/as an addition to” in box “Meta information”:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20831\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"317\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response.jpg\" data-size=\"317x304\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20831\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-response.jpg\" alt=\"Anyone can reply to the post author with a article, announcement, etc\" width=\"317\" height=\"304\" /></a> Anyone can reply to the post author with a article, announcement, etc[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-shareandcontact\">Contacting users, Sharing content</h2>\r\nUsers can interact with each other, all content in the website can be easily shared through different means.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-mentions\">@Mentions</h3>\r\nWhen creating a post or adding a comment, you can mention any user, and this person will receive a notification and an email. Simply type “@” and then start typing the name of the person, and select him/her from the dropdown list:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23249\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/03/mentions.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-23249 size-full\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/03/mentions.jpg\" alt=\"@Mentions\" width=\"300\" height=\"218\" /></a> @Mentions[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sendmsg\">Send a message to another user</h3>\r\nIf you need to contact any user on our website, you can do so. Simply click on the \"Send message\" button, type your message on the new window, and click \"Send\". The user will get your message by email.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20906\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"473\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-sendmessage.jpg\" data-size=\"473x381\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20906\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-sendmessage.jpg\" alt=\"Send a message to any user\" width=\"473\" height=\"381\" /></a> Send a message to any user[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sm\">Social media, Share by email</h3>\r\nShare on Facebook, Twitter, or by email:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20818\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-postoptions.jpg\" data-size=\"709x230\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20818\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-postoptions-640x208.jpg\" alt=\"Share posts on Facebook, Twitter or by email\" width=\"640\" height=\"208\" /></a> Share posts on Facebook, Twitter or by email[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-embed\">Embed</h3>\r\nAll content in the website can be easily embedded on your own website:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20911\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embedlink.jpg\" data-size=\"713x268\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20911\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embedlink-640x241.jpg\" alt=\"Link to embed content\" width=\"640\" height=\"241\" /></a> Link to embed content[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20817\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"599\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embed.jpg\" data-size=\"599x511\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20817\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-embed.jpg\" alt=\"Embed any content on your own website\" width=\"599\" height=\"511\" /></a> Embed any content on your own website[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id=\"howtouse-features\">Website features</h2>\r\nThe features below are thought for giving the users endless possibilities in exploring all the content in the website, from accessing it in different languages, to filtering, to keeping all open pages readily accessible.\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-hashtags\">#Hashtags</h3>\r\nWhen creating a post or adding a comment, you can add a Twitter-like hashtag. Simply type # and the topic, and all posts/comments can be grouped by hashtag/topic. #ripessasia #websitefeatures\r\n\r\nTo see a list of all existing hashtags, simply start typing the #hashtag in your post or comment, and a list will appear:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23335\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"449\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-hashtag.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23335\" data-size=\"449x396\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23335\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-hashtag.jpg\" alt=\"Adding a #hashtag\" width=\"449\" height=\"396\" /></a> Adding a #hashtag[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-volunteering\">Volunteering</h3>\r\nIn sections <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/projects/\">Projects</a>, <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/announcements/\">Announcements</a> and <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/events/\">Events</a>, the author of the post can invite volunteers to participate in their causes:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23327\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"522\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-clicktovolunteer.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23327\" data-size=\"522x402\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23327\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-clicktovolunteer.jpg\" alt=\"Click to Volunteer\" width=\"522\" height=\"402\" /></a> Click to Volunteer[/caption]\r\n\r\nUpon submitting the form, the organizers will get the volunteer\'s information and contact details:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23328\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"420\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-volunteer.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23328\" data-size=\"420x385\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23328\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-volunteer.jpg\" alt=\"Volunteer\'s data is sent to the organizers\" width=\"420\" height=\"385\" /></a> Volunteer\'s data is sent to the organizers[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-lang\">Multiple languages</h3>\r\nThe website frame has been translated to 4 languages: English, Malay, Tamil and Chinese (due to constant website updates, the translations might not be 100% complete or accurate). To access these, the links are visible on the homepage:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23336\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"612\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-languages.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23336\" data-size=\"612x43\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-23336\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-languages.jpg\" alt=\"Multiple languages\" width=\"612\" height=\"43\" /></a> Multiple languages[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-feed\">Content feed</h3>\r\nThe homepage of the website is already a feed of all SSE-related content. Keep scrolling down, keep reading all content posted by all our users.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-search\">Searching, quick access to tags, users\' profiles and content</h3>\r\nOn the top navigation bar, there is a search input. Typing in allows to select the users\' profile, post or tag very quickly, or perform a search of users or content on the website:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-search.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23340\" data-size=\"691x576\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23340\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-search-640x533.jpg\" alt=\"Searching / quick access to tags, users and content\" width=\"640\" height=\"533\" /></a> Searching / quick access to tags, users and content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-filter\">Filter information tags, categories and others</h3>\r\nSince when creating any post the user can select tags, categories it applies to, and other metadata, then all content can be filtered using these parameters:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_23341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-filtering.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-23341\" data-size=\"863x450\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-23341\" src=\"http://uploads.ripessasia.org/wp-content/uploads/getpop-demo/2016/04/ripess-filtering-640x334.jpg\" alt=\"Fiterling content\" width=\"640\" height=\"334\" /></a> Fiterling content[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-tabs\">Browsing history</h3>\r\nAnytime you open any page in the website, a tab to access it again will be created. To access all open pages, click on the timer icon on the top navigation bar (with title “Toggle Browsing History”) to see all tabs. Then, clicking on each tab will take you back to that page:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20848\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-tabs.jpg\" data-size=\"1093x80\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20848\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-tabs-640x47.jpg\" alt=\"Browsing history: all tabs with open pages\" width=\"640\" height=\"47\" /></a> Browsing history: all tabs with open pages[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-navigator\">Navigator</h3>\r\nThe navigator is a way to browse all content on the website, allowing the user to keep open and visible the list of posts to browse. All sections on the website can be opened in the Navigator. To use it, toggle open the navigation menu by clicking on the menu icon, on the top navigation bar, and then on each section link there is a right arrow with tooltip text \"Navigate\". Simply click there, and a left panel, containing all posts for that section, will open on the left side. Clicking on each of the posts will not close the Navigator.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20909\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"291\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigatelink.jpg\" data-size=\"291x132\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20909\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigatelink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to open the Navigator for a given section\" width=\"291\" height=\"132\" /></a> Link to open the Navigator for a given section[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20908\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"329\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigator.jpg\" data-size=\"329x885\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20908\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-navigator.jpg\" alt=\"Navigator\" width=\"329\" height=\"885\" /></a> Navigator[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-sideinfo\">Side information</h3>\r\nEach post\'s meta-information shows on top of each post, and also on the Side information panel. To open it, on the top right corner of the post, there is an \"Options\" button, with a drop-down menu. On this menu, click on \"Information\", and the Side information panel will appear from the right side.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20919\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"164\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-informationlink.jpg\" data-size=\"164x118\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20919\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-informationlink.jpg\" alt=\"Link to open the post information\" width=\"164\" height=\"118\" /></a> Link to open the post information[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20918\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"295\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-information.jpg\" data-size=\"295x837\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-20918\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-information.jpg\" alt=\"Post information\" width=\"295\" height=\"837\" /></a> Post information[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-views\">Multiple view options</h3>\r\nThere are several ways to browse the Content feed:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Full view</li>\r\n	<li>Details (this is the default view)</li>\r\n	<li>List</li>\r\n	<li>Thumbnail</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition, events and users have an additional view:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20820\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventsmap.jpg\" data-size=\"1057x517\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20820\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventsmap-640x313.jpg\" alt=\"Events Map view\" width=\"640\" height=\"313\" /></a> Events Map view[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou can change the default view on the Settings: click on the right-most element on the top navigation bar, and select your preferred option:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20822\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-settings.jpg\" data-size=\"899x322\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20822\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-settings-640x229.jpg\" alt=\"Website settings\" width=\"640\" height=\"229\" /></a> Website settings[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-calendar\">Events calendar</h3>\r\nAll events can be visualized in a lovely <a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/calendar/\">Events Calendar</a>:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_20819\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<a href=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventscalendar.jpg\" data-size=\"1057x517\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-20819\" src=\"http://media.tppdebate.org/wp-content/uploads/tppdebate/2015/12/tppdebate-eventscalendar-640x313.jpg\" alt=\"Events Calendar\" width=\"640\" height=\"313\" /></a> Events Calendar[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 id=\"howtouse-stayingconnected\">Staying connected</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/invite-users/\">Invite your friends to join RIPESS Asia!</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/newsletter/\">Subscribe to RIPESS Asia\'s newsletter campaigns</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://popdemo.localhost/en/contact-us/\">Contact us</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:]','[:en]How to use the website[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','20810-revision-v1','','','2016-04-10 13:02:51','2016-04-10 05:02:51','',20810,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/20810-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(23384,851,'2016-04-23 19:23:43','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-04-23 19:23:43','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/?p=23384',0,'post','',0,0),(23234,851,'2016-03-24 14:04:09','2016-03-24 06:04:09','','[:en]Tags[:es]Tags[:zh]标签[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','tags','','','2016-03-24 14:04:09','2016-03-24 06:04:09','',0,'http://popdemo.localhost/?page_id=23234',0,'page','',0,0),(23235,851,'2016-03-24 14:04:09','2016-03-24 06:04:09','','Tags','','inherit','closed','closed','','23234-revision-v1','','','2016-03-24 14:04:09','2016-03-24 06:04:09','',23234,'http://popdemo.localhost/whatsthis/23234-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0,0),(23237,851,'2016-03-24 17:17:28','2016-03-24 09:17:28','','[:en]Tags[:es]Tags[:zh]标签[:]','','publish','closed','closed','','tags','','','2016-03-24 17:17:28','2016-03-24 09:17:28','',20225,'http://popdemo.localhost/?page_id=23237',0,'page','',0,0),(23238,851,'2016-03-24 17:17:28','2016-03-24 09:17:28','','[:en]Tags[:]','','inherit','closed